    "summary": "As a lawyer at Stibbe I act for companies, developers and public bodies, such as municipalities, provinces, education and other public institutions, representing them in negotiations and before the Dutch and European courts. \n\nMy specialisations include general administrative law, financial public law (subsidies), compliance and sanctions, planning and zoning, environmental law, expropriation, governmental liability, public access to governmental documents, public transport and aviation. Furthermore, I specialise in public law litigation, fundamental human rights, state aid, European administrative law and education law. \n\nIn addition I hold a part-time professorship in constitutional and administrative law at Leiden University. I publish and teach on several administrative law issues. I am a member of the executive board of the Dutch Administrative Law Association and the board of editors of the Dutch Magazine for lawyers (Nederlands Juristenblad).",
